      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "*`Operator` Objects and Evaluation*\n",
        "\n",
        "* When we perform arithmetic with fields, the result is not a field, but an operator object\n",
        "* For example, the expression might symbolically represent â€œadd 1 to the product of -1, 2, and our fieldâ€\n",
        "* To actually compute the operation, we call the operatorâ€™s `.evaluate()` method\n",
        "* This returns a new field containing the numerical result\n",
        "* ðŸ’¡Important: the dealiasing scale factors set when the basis was instantiated are always applied during operator evaluation"
